Bug fixes and performance improvements. Food Network fans the Food Network app just got a whole lot better! The latest improvements and features make it easier than ever to satisfy your appetite for your favorite shows and chefs. Here s what s new: We ve added 1000 s of episodes from current and classic Food Network shows. Now you can watch every episode ever from some of your favorites! New episodes are available at the same time they air on TV. Search for shows by genre. Plus a new look and layout to boot. We ll also be able to make updates much quicker to keep giving you the best app experience possible. Love the app Let us know! Have a question Reach out to app watchfoodnetwork foodnetwork.com

Bug fixes and minor enhancements
See more watch more: Favorites section now has more scrolling room on iPhones to browse latest episodes from shows you pick Bug fixes

Get started with Favorites: We ve made it even easier to pick the shows you love and set up your Favorites. Just tap the heart button on the bottom menu bar and select your shows. Save your picks and the latest episodes from your Favorites will always be waiting for you when they become available. Bug fixes

AirPlay! When playing a video tap the AirPlay icon to watch through your Apple TV. This provides a much better experience than mirroring. Tip: When using AirPlay the Apple TV Remote controls volume and closed captions. TV Schedule is back and better than ever. Find it under the More menu button at the bottom of the screen. Bonus: When an episode on the TV grid is already in the app tap the Watch Now button to start watching without waiting. Fixes sign in problems reported by some users trying to select their TV service provider
